<P><HI>The LORD &s;hall rejoice in his</HI> Works.</P>
<P>A <HI>SERMON</HI> Preach'd at the LECTURE in <HI>BOSTON, Augu&s;t</HI> 27. 1741. BEFORE His EXCELLENCY <HI>William Shirley,</HI> <ABBR>E&s;q</ABBR> Captain-General and Commander in Chief, And in the Audience OF THE General Court.</P>
<P>By <HI>Benjamin Colman,</HI> D.D</P>
<Q><BIBL>PSAL. cxi. 3.</BIBL> <HI>His Work is honourable and glorious, and his Righ|teou&s;ne&s;s endureth for ever.</HI></Q>
<P><HI>BOSTON:</HI> Printed by J. DRAPER, Printer to His Excellency the GOVERNOUR and COUNCIL. MDCCXLI.</P>
</DIV1>
