<HEAD><HI>At a</HI> Council <HI>held at the Council Cham|ber in</HI> Bo&s;ton, <HI>upon Thur&s;day the</HI> 27th <HI>of</HI> Augu&s;t 1741.</HEAD>
<OPENER>Voted,</OPENER>
<P>THAT <HI>Jacob Wendell, Richard Bill</HI> and <HI>John Read,</HI> <ABBR>E&s;qrs</ABBR> be de&s;ired to give the Reverend Dr. <HI>Benjamin Colman</HI> the Thanks of this Board for his <HI>Sermon</HI> preached this Day at the publick <HI>Lecture</HI> in <HI>Bo&s;ton,</HI> and to reque&s;t of him a <HI>Copy</HI> thereof for the Pre&s;s.</P>
